Conclusion:
Because my priorities strongly favor early‑60s, guitar‑forward, mono‑friendly, punchy presentations with close, lead‑vocal‑forward mixes, tight harmonies, 2–4‑minute songcraft, minimal/subtle remastering that preserves dynamics and analog character, the Classic British‑Invasion pressing is the better match. The piano‑led studio album is appealing in its intimacy and vocal focus but deviates in instrumentation (piano and strings/horns), slightly longer song lengths, and overall aesthetic from the core attributes I value most, so I reject it in favor of the British‑Invasion pressing.

